		ol {margin: 5px; padding: 0px 15px;}
		</style>
		</head>
		<body>

		<h1> How it all begun </h1> <hr>

		Chrono technology has been in development for centuries, based on pieces of ancient technology discovered by a group of terrorists
		called the "Technomancers", many companies attempted to take advantage of what they managed to salvage from their attacks.
		Pieces of armor, nuggets of their power-cores, their recognizable catalog... Whatever it could be found was turned into materials
		for RnD investigation. <br><br>

		After a great attack which destroyed the Magna Station headquarters, a council was called by the various companies, they had to stop
		these terrorists from getting their way, cooperating and joining efforts, they went to war against the terrorists under the name
		of the United Stations, creating a network of reinforcements and retaliation against the attacks, during this spacial era, technology
		had a surge in development, as the stations were more able to capture Technomancers alive and their equipments intact, their power grew
		as the Technomancer force diminished. <br><br>

		After the war was over, the United Stations emerged victorious, with technology never seen before in their hands, they were set up
		for a new age... But greed took over them, as the United Stations started to fight in between them for the control of the greatest techs.
		In just a few years, the great United Stations were splitted up again, with their knowledge being spied upon, stolen, fighting for supremacy,
		just as they did before they were allies against a common enemy... <br><br>

		<h2> 110 Years later </h2> <hr>

		Omegacorp raised from the ashes, leaded by a ralentless commander named Igor Pavlov, the company which back in the day was focused
		on teleportation and bluespace technology and was shut down after being sued by Hefastos, claiming that they used their hardware without permission.
		Today, Omegacorp has turned into the first Time Travelling company, an idea discarded in years past due to how unstable and seemingly useless
		the Technomancer's time travelling technology seemed, but Igor Pavlov had a plan for his idea... <br><br>

		Omegacorp's workers receive a generous amount of salary and have unique and amazing experiences each day, and the company itself treats their
		employees with great amounts of free days and holidays... The catch? Not even one worker knows what they are truly working for, the company keeps
		them informed of how they attempt to "document" different history timelines, and it's true, that's one of the things workers do, they document the timelines.
		<br><br>

		But Igor Pavlov has deals with both the Space Police, several people willing to pay immense amounts of money, and even war criminals, he deals
		in timeline changes, artifact handling, historical contraband and many feats impossible to do without time travel... Other companies have attempted
		to sue Omegacorp once again, but this time Igor has made sure to have the law in his side, by creating an official franchise with his work. <br><br>

		Lately, the greatest of timelines has been discovered, a timeline where magic actually exists, a timeline where it's been identified an area in the universe
		where humans and various strange species live together under the protection of this strange energies... Very few information has been leaked out of this timeline,
		and so, Igor's best employees, alongisde with some Space Police commandos, have been sent in a mission, a very specific mission, to discover this place as best
		as they can.

		</body>

		"}

